glassie
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:A glass marble, usu. transparent; occas. a clear glass marble-stopper from early aerated-water bottles. Compare bottlie, glass alley.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1918-20 Auckland man 66 years old  (p.c. Prof. Graeme Kennedy). Common in Auckland when he was a boy. -->1951 14 M 14 St Bede's, Chch 21 GLASSIES [games]
